This paper is about reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper presents a new algorithm for predicting the performance of a reinforcement learning policy given historical data. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the use of models and importance sampling, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper also deals with data analysis and estimation, which are relevant to data science (cs.DS). Finally, the paper's focus on policy evaluation is relevant to control systems (cs.SY).
